00:04:01.600 --> 00:04:03.350
Now, the Tradition was a

00:04:03.370 --> 00:04:05.540
polytheistic religion, meaning

00:04:05.670 --> 00:04:07.939
that it had lots of different gods.

00:04:08.690 --> 00:04:12.049
The most powerful of these gods was Odin,

00:04:12.119 --> 00:04:15.140
the god of wisdom, magic and poetry.

00:04:15.870 --> 00:04:18.073
He was an old man with a beard, who

00:04:18.279 --> 00:04:21.590
was blind in one eye, rode a horse with

00:04:21.610 --> 00:04:25.169
eight legs, and had two pet ravens who

00:04:25.670 --> 00:04:27.829
perched, who sat, on either shoulder.

00:04:28.930 --> 00:04:31.849
Odin’s wife was a goddess named Frigg.

00:04:32.560 --> 00:04:36.040
Just like him, she was very wise, and she

00:04:36.040 --> 00:04:38.400
even had the power to see into the future.

00:04:39.740 --> 00:04:42.290
Odin and Frigg had several children.

00:04:42.809 --> 00:04:44.360
One of these children was

00:04:45.020 --> 00:04:46.430
Thor, the god of thunder.

00:04:46.910 --> 00:04:48.909
He was brave and strong, with

00:04:48.910 --> 00:04:51.150
a magical hammer which returned

00:04:51.170 --> 00:04:53.030
to his hand after he threw it.

00:04:54.000 --> 00:04:56.140
And their other child was Balder.

00:04:56.710 --> 00:04:59.090
He was known as the most beautiful of

00:04:59.130 --> 00:05:02.840
all the gods, so pure and perfect that

00:05:02.840 --> 00:05:04.439
he couldn’t be damaged by anything.

00:05:04.980 --> 00:05:06.900
Well, there was one thing, but

00:05:06.990 --> 00:05:08.230
we’ll get to that in a minute.

00:05:09.700 --> 00:05:12.270
Then there was Loki, the god of

00:05:12.290 --> 00:05:15.049
chaos and trickery, a naughty god who

00:05:15.190 --> 00:05:17.599
wasn’t so keen on following the rules.

00:05:18.370 --> 00:05:21.349
Sometimes, he acted as an ally, a

00:05:21.460 --> 00:05:23.669
friend, to the other gods, helping

00:05:23.670 --> 00:05:25.719
them to come up with clever plans.

00:05:26.700 --> 00:05:29.580
At other times, he tricked the other gods.

00:05:30.640 --> 00:05:33.799
The most famous of Loki’s tricks, if

00:05:33.809 --> 00:05:35.989
you can really call it a trick, was the

00:05:35.990 --> 00:05:39.669
murder of Balder, who remember, was Odin

00:05:39.669 --> 00:05:42.209
and Frigg’s perfect son, the one who

00:05:42.209 --> 00:05:44.530
couldn’t be damaged or hurt by anything.

00:05:45.440 --> 00:05:48.150
Anything, that is, except for a

00:05:48.180 --> 00:05:50.700
piece of mistletoe, a poisonous

00:05:50.720 --> 00:05:53.030
plant with white berries, the one

00:05:53.160 --> 00:05:55.340
people kiss under at Christmas time.

00:05:56.520 --> 00:05:59.630
When Loki learned about Balder’s weakness,

00:05:59.790 --> 00:06:02.480
he tricked one of the other gods into

00:06:02.480 --> 00:06:05.160
throwing a piece of mistletoe at Balder.

00:06:06.460 --> 00:06:09.380
Balder was killed, and when Odin

00:06:09.420 --> 00:06:11.490
found out what had happened, he

00:06:11.490 --> 00:06:14.940
was furious, and set out to punish

00:06:14.940 --> 00:06:16.900
Loki in the most terrible way.

00:06:18.389 --> 00:06:20.760
According to the stories, Loki was

00:06:20.760 --> 00:06:23.630
tied to a rock and dropped into a

00:06:23.630 --> 00:06:27.050
cave, where a venomous snake would drip

00:06:27.160 --> 00:06:30.230
poison on his face for all eternity.

00:06:31.440 --> 00:06:33.590
There were plenty of other gods as well.

00:06:33.599 --> 00:06:36.400
Hel, the goddess of death,

00:06:36.510 --> 00:06:38.690
who only had half a face.

00:06:39.630 --> 00:06:42.109
Tyr, the god of warriors, whose

00:06:42.240 --> 00:06:44.780
hand was bitten off by a giant wolf.

00:06:45.610 --> 00:06:48.470
Freya, the goddess of love and beauty,

00:06:48.630 --> 00:06:51.549
who rode a chariot pulled by cats.

