Most people don’t even realise they’re

00:13:20.208 --> 00:13:22.398
doing it, but there’s a good chance that

00:13:22.398 --> 00:13:25.418
an English speaker unwittingly mentions

00:13:25.438 --> 00:13:28.238
a Norse god at least once every day.

00:13:29.428 --> 00:13:31.098
We can also see its influence

00:13:31.308 --> 00:13:33.198
very strongly in stories.

00:13:33.628 --> 00:13:35.928
This ancient religion has inspired

00:13:35.928 --> 00:13:37.408
some of the most successful

00:13:37.588 --> 00:13:39.888
books and films ever made.

00:13:40.508 --> 00:13:41.958
If you look at a list of the

00:13:42.028 --> 00:13:44.008
bestselling books of all time,

00:13:44.168 --> 00:13:46.788
you’ll find JRR Tolkein’s The

00:13:46.798 --> 00:13:48.448
Lord of the Rings at number three.

00:13:48.948 --> 00:13:52.288
It has sold over 150 million copies

00:13:52.518 --> 00:13:56.478
since it was published in 1954.

00:13:56.478 --> 00:13:57.658
Perhaps you bought one of them,

00:13:57.938 --> 00:14:00.078
and if you didn't, you may well

00:14:00.078 --> 00:14:01.478
have watched the films instead.

00:14:02.608 --> 00:14:05.288
If you know the story, either by reading

00:14:05.288 --> 00:14:07.398
the book or watching the films, you

00:14:07.398 --> 00:14:09.798
may well have noticed some similarities

00:14:09.818 --> 00:14:12.288
between the characters in Tolkein’s books

00:14:12.458 --> 00:14:15.058
and some of the gods I described earlier.

00:14:15.548 --> 00:14:17.818
Tolkein was incredibly

00:14:17.928 --> 00:14:20.008
interested in Norse mythology.

00:14:20.468 --> 00:14:22.568
He started a group called The

00:14:22.568 --> 00:14:24.598
Viking Club, where he would study

00:14:24.618 --> 00:14:26.398
Norse mythology with his friends.

00:14:26.888 --> 00:14:29.118
And these Norse influences

00:14:29.388 --> 00:14:31.418
are everywhere in his writing.

00:14:32.648 --> 00:14:34.838
Remember, in Norse mythology there

00:14:34.838 --> 00:14:37.588
are different races: gods, humans,

00:14:37.748 --> 00:14:40.448
giants, elves, trolls and dwarves.

00:14:40.958 --> 00:14:44.038
In Norse mythology, the dwarves lived

00:14:44.048 --> 00:14:46.338
in mountains and deep underground.

00:14:46.718 --> 00:14:48.398
They were famous for their

00:14:48.568 --> 00:14:49.968
mining and metalwork.

00:14:50.468 --> 00:14:52.998
In Norse mythology, the elves had

00:14:53.008 --> 00:14:55.968
magical powers and supernatural beauty.

00:14:56.718 --> 00:14:59.118
In Norse mythology, there was Odin,

00:14:59.168 --> 00:15:01.308
the wise old man with the beard.

00:15:02.068 --> 00:15:04.898
If you have read any Tolkein, and you know

00:15:04.898 --> 00:15:06.828
the story of Lord of the Rings, you will

00:15:06.828 --> 00:15:09.408
be able to clearly see the links between

00:15:09.408 --> 00:15:12.298
Tolkein’s world and the real, or at

00:15:12.298 --> 00:15:15.228
least believed, world of Norse mythology.

00:15:16.058 --> 00:15:17.788
And this is also true for

00:15:17.788 --> 00:15:19.218
hundreds of other books.

00:15:19.558 --> 00:15:21.738
Norse mythology’s magical races

00:15:21.918 --> 00:15:24.168
have inspired so many authors,

00:15:24.348 --> 00:15:26.708
including another of the best-selling

00:15:26.708 --> 00:15:28.328
writers of all time, one that

00:15:28.498 --> 00:15:31.243
came a little later: JK Rowling.

00:15:31.808 --> 00:15:34.198
If you’ve read Harry Potter, or

00:15:34.348 --> 00:15:35.938
you've seen the movies, you’ll

00:15:35.938 --> 00:15:37.668
remember that there are elves

00:15:37.668 --> 00:15:39.998
and giants, and a wise old man.

00:15:40.948 --> 00:15:43.238
Rowling even named one of her characters,

00:15:43.378 --> 00:15:46.558
an evil werewolf, Fenrir Greyback.

00:15:47.538 --> 00:15:49.778
If you think back to the wolf I mentioned

00:15:49.868 --> 00:15:52.758
earlier, the one who bit off Tyr’s hand.

00:15:53.198 --> 00:15:55.948
That wolf was also called Fenrir.

00:15:56.708 --> 00:15:59.498
So, these influences are everywhere

00:15:59.598 --> 00:16:01.008
if you look carefully enough.

00:16:01.938 --> 00:16:04.088
And in some cases, you don’t even

00:16:04.088 --> 00:16:05.838
have to look carefully at all.

00:16:06.628 --> 00:16:08.698
If you are a fan of Marvel,

00:16:08.748 --> 00:16:10.438
you’ll know that two of the main

00:16:10.438 --> 00:16:12.928
characters are Thor and Loki.

00:16:13.638 --> 00:16:16.058
Just like the Thor in Norse mythology,

00:16:16.368 --> 00:16:19.108
the Thor in the Marvel movies is the god

00:16:19.278 --> 00:16:22.048
of thunder, with a magical hammer which

00:16:22.108 --> 00:16:24.478
returns to his hand after he throws it.

00:16:25.338 --> 00:16:28.088
His father is Odin, his mother is Frigg,

00:16:28.318 --> 00:16:30.728
and he comes from a world called Asgard.

00:16:32.208 --> 00:16:34.498
And as for Loki, he’s the son of a

00:16:34.498 --> 00:16:36.958
giant, who sometimes works on Thor’s

00:16:36.958 --> 00:16:39.578
side, and at other times betrays him.

00:16:40.038 --> 00:16:42.348
It’s pretty much the same story,

00:16:42.528 --> 00:16:44.548
with a 21st century twist!

00:16:45.578 --> 00:16:48.148
And now, before we finish, we just

00:16:48.148 --> 00:16:50.268
have time for another interesting

00:16:50.268 --> 00:16:52.348
fact about the impact of the

00:16:52.348 --> 00:16:54.108
vikings on the modern world.

00:16:54.628 --> 00:16:57.568
And this is a legacy that you may well

00:16:57.578 --> 00:17:00.898
be using at this very moment, if you are

00:17:00.898 --> 00:17:02.868
listening to this with headphones without

00:17:02.878 --> 00:17:05.848
wires, on AirPods or something like that.

00:17:06.638 --> 00:17:08.088
I’m talking about Bluetooth,

00:17:08.568 --> 00:17:10.258
the wireless technology.

00:17:11.268 --> 00:17:13.483
Bluetooth was named after a

00:17:13.483 --> 00:17:15.697
Viking king, Harald Bluetooth.

00:17:16.127 --> 00:17:18.207
He was the King of Denmark at the end

00:17:18.397 --> 00:17:20.657
of the 10th century, and he wasn’t

00:17:20.697 --> 00:17:22.907
particularly good at brushing his teeth.

00:17:23.817 --> 00:17:26.317
One tooth got so rotten

00:17:26.377 --> 00:17:27.597
that it turned blue.

00:17:28.047 --> 00:17:29.997
That’s where this nickname comes from.

00:17:30.607 --> 00:17:33.787
So, why name this technology after

00:17:33.787 --> 00:17:35.907
this dentist-hating Danish king?

00:17:36.657 --> 00:17:39.327
Well, Harald Bluetooth was famous

00:17:39.337 --> 00:17:41.957
for connecting Denmark and Norway

00:17:41.957 --> 00:17:44.517
into one kingdom, just like Bluetooth

00:17:44.547 --> 00:17:47.877
technology connects phones to computers

00:17:47.907 --> 00:17:49.607
or headphones or things like that.

00:17:50.367 --> 00:17:52.987
If you are listening to this episode via

00:17:52.987 --> 00:17:55.567
Bluetooth, or you have a Bluetooth-enabled

00:17:55.567 --> 00:17:57.897
phone or computer nearby, take a

00:17:57.897 --> 00:18:00.417
look at the Bluetooth logo now.

00:18:01.337 --> 00:18:03.847
It looks a bit like two triangles

00:18:03.897 --> 00:18:05.857
with lines sticking out of the

00:18:05.857 --> 00:18:07.817
left, or maybe you think it

00:18:07.817 --> 00:18:10.057
looks a bit like the letter “B”.

00:18:10.777 --> 00:18:13.727
The Bluetooth logo is actually a

00:18:13.767 --> 00:18:17.257
pair of viking runes, or Old Norse

00:18:17.267 --> 00:18:19.917
symbols - Hagall and Bjarkan.

00:18:20.267 --> 00:18:21.927
H and B, if you were to

00:18:22.147 --> 00:18:23.417
convert them to English.

00:18:24.337 --> 00:18:26.807
These letters were Harald Bluetooth’s

00:18:26.837 --> 00:18:29.357
initials, his initials now forever

00:18:29.357 --> 00:18:32.217
embedded on a technology used by billions

00:18:32.217 --> 00:18:34.627
of people around the world every day.

00:18:35.767 --> 00:18:38.177
So, next time you turn on your Bluetooth,

00:18:38.337 --> 00:18:41.447
you meet a lady called Freya, or you need

00:18:41.447 --> 00:18:43.937
to arrange anything for a weekday except

00:18:43.967 --> 00:18:46.697
Monday, just remember that the remnants of

00:18:46.697 --> 00:18:49.227
Norse mythology are everywhere around us.

00:18:49.947 --> 00:18:52.097
And if this story has really

00:18:52.097 --> 00:18:54.267
captured you, I’m glad to hear it.

